  "full_text": "4.3.2.6 Determination of Operational Times\nDetermination of Operational Times\n1) Except as provided in Sentence (3), the annual operational time of each space during daytime, tday,i, shall be determined using Table 4.3.2.6.-A.\n2) Except as provided in Sentence (3), the annual operational time of each space during nighttime, tnight,i, shall be determined using Table 4.3.2.6.-B.\n3) If the building operates for more or less than the default 250 days per year, the data provided in Tables 4.3.2.6.-A and 4.3.2.6.-B shall be linearly adjusted using the following equation: [Equation: t_{adjusted} = t_{base} \\times \\frac{d_{operation}}{250}] where tadjusted = adjusted operational time to be used in the trade-off path, in h, tbase = base operational time provided in Table 4.3.2.6.-A or 4.3.2.6.-B, and doperation = actual number of annual days of operation of the building, in days. Table 4.3.2.6.-A Number of Operational Hours of the Building During Daytime, tday,i, for Various Start and End Times Forming Part of Sentences 4.3.2.6.(1) and (3) Operation Start Time Operation End Time 1 a.m. 2 a.m. 3 a.m. 4 a.m. 5 a.m. 6 a.m. 7 a.m. 8 a.m. 9 a.m. 10 a.m. 11 a.m. 12 p.m. 1 p.m. 2 p.m. 3 p.m. 4 p.m. 5 p.m. 6 p.m. 7 p.m. 8 p.m. 9 p.m. 10 p.m. 11 p.m. 12 a.m. t day,i , in h/a 12 a.m. 155 363 613 863 1,113 1,363 1,613 1,863 2,113 2,363 2,580 2,743 2,879 2,979 3,014 3,014 3,014 3,014 1 a.m. 155 363 613 863 1,113 1,363 1,613 1,863 2,113 2,363 2,580 2,743 2,879 2,979 3,014 3,014 3,014 3,014 2 a.m. 155 363 613 863 1,113 1,363 1,613 1,863 2,113 2,363 2,580 2,743 2,879 2,979 3,014 3,014 3,014 3,014 3 a.m. 155 363 613 863 1,113 1,363 1,613 1,863 2,113 2,363 2,580 2,743 2,879 2,979 3,014 3,014 3,014 3,014 4 a.m. 155 363 613 863 1,113 1,363 1,613 1,863 2,113 2,363 2,580 2,743 2,879 2,979 3,014 3,014 3,014 3,014 5 a.m. 155 363 613 863 1,113 1,363 1,613 1,863 2,113 2,363 2,580 2,743 2,879 2,979 3,014 3,014 3,014 3,014 6 a.m. 119 327 577 827 1,077 1,327 1,577 1,827 2,077 2,32